cff-version: 1.2.0
title: hipfire
message: >-
  If you use or build on hipfire, please cite it as below.
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Kaden
    family-names: Schutt
    email: kaden@hipfire.dev
    affiliation: Independent
repository-code: 'https://github.com/Kaden-Schutt/hipfire'
url: 'https://github.com/Kaden-Schutt/hipfire'
abstract: >-
  hipfire is a Rust-native LLM inference engine for AMD RDNA / CDNA
  GPUs. It targets the full RDNA1 -> RDNA4 family (plus CDNA where
  ROCm support overlaps) without a build-time HIP/ROCm dependency,
  loading libamdhip64 at runtime via dlopen. The engine ships an
  original quantization family (HFQ4-G256, MagnumQuant MQ4/MQ8 with
  offline FWHT rotation, HFP4/MFP4 FP4), an asym3 KV cache with
  asym-aware flash attention, and a DDTree-RDNA tree-speculative
  decode path on top of DFlash. See PRIOR-ART.md for the full
  inventory of original architectural innovations with first-commit
  dates and canonical hashes.
keywords:
  - inference
  - llm
  - amd
  - rdna
  - rocm
  - hip
  - rust
  - quantization
  - speculative-decoding
  - flash-attention
license: MIT OR Apache-2.0
version: 0.2.0
date-released: '2026-05-27'
